{{!--
{
  "layout": "standard",
  "title": "Vibes DIY Blog | Notes from the build log",
  "description": "Field notes, evals, and stories from building Vibes DIY — the no-code app builder that turns a sentence into a working app.",
  "ogUrl": "https://good.vibes.diy/blog/",
  "source": "blog-index"
}
--}}

<style>
        @import url('https://fonts.cdnfonts.com/css/alte-haas-grotesk');

        :root {
            --os-gray: #7A7A7A;
            --grid-gray: #CCCDC8;
            --goldenrod: #FEDD00;
            --ruby: #DA291C;
            --bluey: #009ACE;
            --ivory: #FFFFF0;
            --black: #231F20;
            --white: #FFFFFF;
            --grid-line: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
        }

        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

        body {
            font-family: 'Alte Haas Grotesk', sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--grid-gray);
            color: var(--black);
            line-height: 1.6;
            background-image:
                linear-gradient(var(--grid-line) 1px, transparent 1px),
                linear-gradient(90deg, var(--grid-line) 1px, transparent 1px);
            background-size: 40px 40px;
            min-height: 100vh;
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
        }

        header {
            padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            position: sticky;
            top: 0;
            z-index: 100;
            background: linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--grid-gray) 60%, transparent);
        }
        .logo-link { display: block; text-decoration: none; }
        .logo-img { height: 72px; width: auto; display: block; }
        .mono { font-family: 'SFMono-Regular', 'Menlo', 'Consolas', monospace; }

        .blog-wrap { max-width: 980px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 1rem 1.5rem 4rem; }

        .blog-masthead {
            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
        }
        .blog-overline {
            font-size: 0.72rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.28em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--os-gray);
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        }
        .blog-masthead h1 {
            font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 6vw, 4rem);
            font-weight: bold;
            line-height: 1.0;
            letter-spacing: -0.03em;
            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
        }
        .blog-masthead p {
            color: var(--os-gray);
            font-size: 1.15rem;
            max-width: 56ch;
        }

        .post-list { display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; }

        .post-item {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
            background: var(--white);
            border: 3px solid var(--black);
            border-radius: 20px;
            box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--black);
            overflow: hidden;
            text-decoration: none;
            color: var(--black);
            transition: transform 0.18s ease, box-shadow 0.18s ease;
        }
        .post-item:hover { transform: translate(-3px, -3px); box-shadow: 9px 9px 0 var(--black); }
        .post-thumb { background: #e8e8e0; min-height: 220px; }
        .post-thumb img { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block; }
        .post-thumb.glyph {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            background:
                linear-gradient(135deg, #0b3a4a 0%, #231f20 100%),
                repeating-linear-gradient(0deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.04) 0 1px, transparent 1px 40px);
            color: var(--goldenrod);
            font-family: 'SFMono-Regular', 'Menlo', 'Consolas', monospace;
            font-size: 2.6rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .post-body { padding: 1.85rem 1.85rem 1.65rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
        .post-date {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.16em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--bluey);
            margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
        }
        .post-item h2 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            line-height: 1.12;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
        }
        .post-item p { color: #555; font-size: 0.97rem; flex: 1; }
        .post-readmore { margin-top: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--bluey); font-size: 0.9rem; }

        @media (max-width: 680px) {
            .post-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .post-thumb { min-height: 180px; }
        }
    </style>

<main class="blog-wrap">
    <div class="blog-masthead">
        <div class="blog-overline mono">// the build log</div>
        <h1>Vibes DIY Blog</h1>
        <p>Field notes, evals, and stories from building the no-code app builder that turns a sentence into a working app.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="post-list">

        <a href="upgrading-apps-with-screenshots.html" class="post-item">
            <div class="post-thumb glyph">look&nbsp;→&nbsp;fix&nbsp;→&nbsp;push&nbsp;↺</div>
            <div class="post-body">
                <div class="post-date mono">June 9, 2026</div>
                <h2>How we batch-upgrade apps with screenshots</h2>
                <p>Every deployed Vibe serves both a live screenshot and its own source. That closes a visual feedback loop an agent can run alone — see the app, fix the code, push, look again — and fan out across dozens of apps at once.</p>
                <span class="post-readmore">Read the post →</span>
            </div>
        </a>

        <a href="how-we-eval-the-generator.html" class="post-item">
            <div class="post-thumb">
                <img src="{{assetPrefix}}images/blog/eval-process/goals-enh-after.png" alt="A role-gated team board generated from a plain-language prompt during an eval run" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <div class="post-body">
                <div class="post-date mono">June 9, 2026</div>
                <h2>How we eval the generator</h2>
                <p>Every edit to the system prompt changes every app anyone generates. Here's the harness that measures generation quality — 46 prompts in three sets, scored 1–5, fanned out across a Workflow pipeline — so we know within a coffee break whether a change made things better or worse.</p>
                <span class="post-readmore">Read the post →</span>
            </div>
        </a>

        <a href="can-a-prompt-rebuild-the-pickathon-app.html" class="post-item">
            <div class="post-thumb">
                <img src="{{assetPrefix}}images/blog/pickathon-prompt-eval/generated-c2-real-data.png" alt="The Pickathon app regenerated from a single prompt, loading the real festival lineup" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <div class="post-body">
                <div class="post-date mono">June 9, 2026</div>
                <h2>Can one English prompt rebuild our festival app?</h2>
                <p>We tried to recreate Pickathon's built-out 2026 app — data model, views, and a fiddly access policy — from a single plain-English prompt. It got ~90% there on description alone; a URL and a one-sentence schema closed the rest.</p>
                <span class="post-readmore">Read the post →</span>
            </div>
        </a>

    </div>
</main>
